On the following day Stephen, with a choaen band of soldiers, and with great ceremony, set about bringing before Edward in London the Duke of Albany along with the other captives, Thomas also being in the procession loaded with irons. He doubtless hoped for a great reward, as he had captured and brought before the king so formidable an enemy. Little did he know how dear Thomas had become to the king on account of his recent services.
